<h1>Spanish Classes Online</h1><p>&nbsp;Casa Xelaju offers online Spanish classes with certified native-speaking instructors from Guatemala. With over 38 years of experience, our teachers are dedicated to helping students learn Spanish as a second language. Classes are delivered through Google Meet, and all lesson materials are shared via Google Drive, providing an interactive and seamless learning experience from anywhere in the world.</p><iframe width="100%" height="550" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OojsXRwfplo" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
<p>&nbsp;Our one-on-one lessons are flexible and tailored to your level, making them ideal for students, travelers, educators, and healthcare workers. The curriculum incorporates cultural immersion, allowing students to experience Guatemalan language and culture from home. Casa Xelaju, established in 1987, currently offers more than 35 online Spanish courses, including test preparation for DELE, OPI, Praxis II, BCLAD, TOPT, FSI, SAT II, CLEP, Content Knowledge 0191, MTEL, and other standardized exams.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Our courses align with the American Council on the Teaching of Foreign Languages (ACTFL) standards, which are used by thousands of universities and school districts worldwide. We are the only program in Guatemala with academic agreements with three major universities in the United States. Tuition for regular Spanish conversation is US$18.00 per hour, while Spanish grammar instruction and OPI test preparation are US$20.00 per hour. Purchasing a 20-hour package grants two free hours. Payments can be made online via PayPal or sent to our Minneapolis office, and students are encouraged to use the code All-I-can-talk-September/october/25 when submitting their application.</p><a href="https://www.casaxelaju.com/spanish-classes-online-skype/"><b><span style="font-size: x-large;">Spanish Classes Online</span></b></a><br />
<p>&nbsp;Online classes simulate an in-person experience, making it easier to maintain and improve your Spanish skills. Our setup through Google Meet is simple, and we recommend using high-quality headphones for the best experience. Classes are available for children, middle and high school students, college students, adults, and teachers.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Cancellations are permitted up to 24 hours before the scheduled session without penalty; same-day cancellations require full tuition. For assistance, students may contact Teresa de Leon at pedrera@cx.edu.gt or call (612) 287-5867.</p>
<p>&nbsp;We also offer specialized Spanish test preparation for DELE, Content Knowledge 0191, MTTC, OSAT, MTEL, ICTS, FTCE, NYSTCE, CLAD/BCLAD, TOPT, Praxis PPST, SAT II, FSI, and Oral Proficiency Interview (OPI). Learning with native speakers enhances pronunciation, cultural understanding, and conversational fluency in real-life situations. Classes are scheduled based on your availability, and students often see strong progress within three to six months with consistent practice. Reviews and testimonials highlight our 100% customer satisfaction.</p>
